  paragraphs:
  - Stop!
  - Ah! Who are you?
  - Those items, what you have just taken... return them. Hand them to me, please.
  - Whatever could you mean by "hand them to you"? I found these items...they are
    mine. They belong to me now, for science!
  - What you have taken from here, from this land...it belongs to my people! They
    have been here for thousands of years undisturbed!
  - And they deserve to be seen by the world, by *my* people! What primitive artifacts
    they are...I have never seen anything more fascinating!
  - The doctor will be more than pleased once I've returned!
  - Be cautious, child. The forest will not let you leave with stolen goods. It watches
    closely and always remembers.
  - What could a forest of trees and simple birds do against me? You speak nonsense,
    woman!
  - Now, I shall take my leave with the items that I have found, and make my way
    back home. Farewell!
  - This is your final warning...please hand over what you took and return them at
    once! You are toying with powers beyond your means...
  - You speak nonsense once again, woman! Now, leave me be at once. Good day to you!
  - You have made your choice, traveler...the forest does not forget, and soon you
    shall discover why...
